aelstrom to replace your icebear cloak.<br><br>If you're dragon/dwarf aligned, quest for the Dragon Tooth choker.  If you're giant, quest for Collar of the Storm. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ugranyte.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Granyte</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(12/25/01 4:56:39 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=13586.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://pages.sprint.ca/granyte/files/profile.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: .</span><hr size=1> Depends I guess on what your guild is capable of doing.<br><br>Personally, I'd try and lead guild raids against trak and VS so you can score some DW legs/BP.  Might be a while though to do it that way.<br><br>In terms of shoulder, currently I'm working on the Strength of Elements quest, requires 3 kills basically, Master Yael, Phinigel and a guy in Western Wastes, then get an easy to find ground drop in Skyfire and presto you got some pretty wicked shoulders.<br><br>As was stated before, you can do the Coldain ring quest if you're alligned with dwarves (at least dubious).  I did the quest twice over the period of a week, using the 8th and 7th rings now, can't use 2 8th since their lore,  however, once I get the 10th ring, the other I'll take to 9th.<br><br>In terms of haste, it's kinda tricky, now there are some wicked belts and cloaks out there that do not have haste components, one example is the 35ac flowing thought 2 cloak from that named robe guy in Maiden's Eye, level 60 and you only need 2 high level groups to take him out.  In terms of belts, last night a group we had over by umbral plains border (in maiden's eye) the Xin Thall Coterie dropped this 20ac 15str 15wis belt....very sweet item, unforunately I'm using the Girdle of Faith as my haste item so I had to pass ;P<br><br>Gloves, boots, arms, definiltey go with the Kael armor quests, 2 groups easy to do giants in arena and by houses.<br><br>Earring, again as mentioned, sarnak earring of station is a pretty descent item and seems to be more common now in Chardok, I'd also get a shrunken goblin skull earring if you got the spare cash, only because that grim aura is always nice for fighting dragons and debuffing mobs you cannot stun.<br><br>Maidens eye also has a nice little necklace that drops, 12ac 5str 15vs magic, 5vs cold and fire and I think some mana.<br><br>You can see my layout on the Magelo file, it's up to date as to what I've worked on, both solo and with guild on raids. <p>Granyte Trueblade 60th Crusader of Brell Serilis<BR><BR>"Give a man a fire and he's warm for a day, but set fire to him and he'swarm for the rest of his life."<BR><BR>/guild who wants Divine Strength?<BR>Durrel tells you "I do."<BR>/tell durrel inc<BR>Ezuin tells you "gimme."<BR>/tell ezuin inc<BR>Vendric tells you "Me plz."<BR>/tell vendric inc<BR>Branven tells you "."<BR>/tell branven inc<BR>Myxin tells you "I do."<BR>/tell myxin not a chance in hell :P<BR><BR><BR><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=43035">Magelo Profile</A><BR><img src = "http://pages.sprint.ca/granyte/files/granytesig.jpg"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uartemecium.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Artemecium</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(12/27/01 3:50:05 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=13586.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: .</span><hr size=1> Kunark bp's and dragon haste command 65